0个基因。但是，这些下调基因中只有9个常见。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">讨论：这些发现支持在干扰基因分析中使用多个数据库。这项研究的结果和科学文献中可用的数据有助于建立生物标志物概况，以识别呼吸敏化剂。</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID： <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40098965/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250318181017&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">40098965</a> | PMC： <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11911524/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250318181017&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11911524</a> | doi： <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1470602>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1470602</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> PubMed：40098965</guid><pubDate> Tue, 18 Mar 2025 06:00:00 -0400</pubDate><dc:creator>泰勒·杰弗里斯（Taylor Jefferis）</dc:creator><dc:creator>詹姆斯·刘</dc:creator><dc:creator>基拉·格里芬（Kiera L Griffin）</dc:creator><dc:creator>马修·吉布（Matthew Gibb）</dc:creator><dc:creator>克里斯蒂·M·赛斯（Christie M Sayes）</dc:creator><dc:date> 2025-03-18</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>对呼吸敏化剂的免疫反应中的基因调控和信号通路：数据库分析</dc:title><dc:identifier>PMID：40098965</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> PMC：PMC11911524</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1470602</dc:identifier></item><item><title>成人免疫经历的小鼠骨再生期间B细胞分化的明显损害</title><link/>https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40098964/?utm_source = chrome&amp;utm_medium = rsss＆utm_camp aign =期刊＆utm_content = 101560960＆fc = none＆ff = 20250318181017＆v = 2.18.0.post9+e462414<description>简介：已显示自适应免疫系统的改变会影响骨骼愈合，并可能导致某些患者的愈合受损。除T细胞外，B细胞是适应性免疫的关键驱动因素。因此，它们在与年龄相关的骨骼愈合损伤中的作用对于理解愈合过程中的延迟可能至关重要。 B细胞对于骨形成至关重要，其功能障碍与衰老或自身免疫性疾病有关。但是是否与年龄相关... </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><p style="color: #4aa564;"><b>前免疫</b>。 2025年3月3日； 16：1511902。 doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1511902。环保2025。</p><p><b>抽象的</b></p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">简介：已显示自适应免疫系统的改变会影响骨骼愈合，并可能导致某些患者的愈合受损。除T细胞外，B细胞是适应性免疫的关键驱动因素。因此，它们在与年龄相关的骨骼愈合损伤中的作用对于理解愈合过程中的延迟可能至关重要。 B细胞对于骨形成至关重要，其功能障碍与衰老或自身免疫性疾病有关。但是，骨骼再生是否涉及与年龄相关的B细胞表型的变化是未知的。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">方法：在这里，我们旨在表征免疫老化在骨骼愈合早期炎症阶段中B细胞表型中的作用。通过比较与年轻和免疫经历的小鼠经历的非免疫性，我们旨在分析获得B细胞的免疫体验的影响。我们的单细胞蛋白基因组分析量化了从截骨后血肿和近端和远端骨髓腔中分离出的细胞的数千个转录组，使我们能够评估细胞比例，差异基因表达和细胞轨迹。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">结果：虽然血肿后截骨后2天的B细胞比例从2天变化为5天，但我们发现免疫经历的小鼠B细胞比例显着降低，伴随着B细胞特异性基因的表达降低，表明在免疫经验丰富的动物中表明了特异性反应。此外，与非免疫和年轻动物相比，我们检测到了免疫经验的小鼠中最广泛的B细胞分化块，主要是从不成熟到成熟的B细胞的过渡。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">讨论：我们的结果表明，在免疫经历的动物中发现的B细胞产生的明显损害在初始阶段起着重要作用，从而导致骨骼愈合延迟。因此，新型的治疗方法可能能够靶向B细胞分化缺陷，即使在免疫经历的环境中也可以保留B细胞功能，这很容易延迟愈合。</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID： <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40098964/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250318181017&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">40098964</a> | PMC： <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11911212/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250318181017&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11911212</a> | doi： <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1511902>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1511902</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> PubMed：40098964</guid><pubDate> Tue, 18 Mar 2025 06:00:00 -0400</pubDate><dc:creator> Mireille ngokingha tchouto</dc:creator><dc:creator>克里斯蒂安·H·布彻（Christian H Bucher）</dc:creator><dc:creator> Ann-Kathrin烂摊子</dc:creator><dc:creator>西蒙·哈斯（Simon Haas）</dc:creator><dc:creator> Katharina Schmidt-Bleek</dc:creator><dc:creator> Georg n Duda</dc:creator><dc:creator> Dieter Beule</dc:creator><dc:creator> Miha Milek</dc:creator><dc:date> 2025-03-18</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>成人免疫经历的小鼠骨再生期间B细胞分化的明显损害</dc:title><dc:identifier>PMID：40098964</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> PMC：PMC11911212</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1511902</dc:identifier></item><item><title> Anti-synthetase syndrome with anti-PL-7 antibody positive in a child: a case report and literature review</title><link/> https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40098963/?utm_source=Chrome&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=journals&amp;utm_content=101560960&amp;fc=None&amp;ff=20250318181017&amp;v=2.18.0.post9+e462414<description> CONCLUSION: This case represents the youngest reported patient with PL-7 positive ASS to date. </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><p style="color: #4aa564;"><b>前免疫</b>。 2025 Mar 3;16:1525432. doi: 10.3389/fimmu.2025.1525432.环保2025。</p><p><b>抽象的</b></p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one"> BACKGROUND: Anti-synthetase syndrome (ASS) is a rare autoimmune myopathy and forms part of the idiopathic inflammatory myopathies (IIMs). A distinctive feature of ASS is the presence of anti-aminoacyl tRNA synthase (ARS) antibodies, which target synthetases, leading to inflammation in muscles, lungs, and other tissues. </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one"> CASE PRESENTATION: A case of a 12-year-old Chinese girl with recurrent fever, myalgia, and Gottron&#39;s papules is reported. Serum creatine kinase was markedly elevated, and chest CT revealed interstitial changes. Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) of the left thigh indicated soft tissue swelling and interstitial fluid accumulation. Electromyography demonstrated myogenic injury. Pathological examination of a left thigh muscle biopsy revealed local edema, focal lymphocyte infiltration, and proliferation and dilation of interstitial small vessels. The myositis antibody spectrum test was positive for anti-PL-7 antibodies. Treatment with glucocorticoids and methotrexate led to significant improvement in her condition. </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one"> CONCLUSION: This case represents the youngest reported patient with PL-7 positive ASS to date.</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID: <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40098963/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250318181017&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">40098963</a> | PMC: <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11911354/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250318181017&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11911354</a> | DOI: <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1525432>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1525432</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> pubmed:40098963</guid><pubDate> Tue, 18 Mar 2025 06:00:00 -0400</pubDate><dc:creator> Jia Liu</dc:creator><dc:creator> Nana Nie</dc:creator><dc:creator> Ranran Zhang</dc:creator><dc:creator> Dahai Wang</dc:creator><dc:creator> Yi Lin</dc:creator><dc:creator> Hong Chang</dc:creator><dc:date> 2025-03-18</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>Anti-synthetase syndrome with anti-PL-7 antibody positive in a child: a case report and literature review</dc:title><dc:identifier> pmid:40098963</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> pmc:PMC11911354</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi:10.3389/fimmu.2025.1525432</dc:identifier></item><item><title> Targeting cGAS-STING: modulating the immune landscape of hepatic diseases</title><link/> https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40098962/?utm_source=Chrome&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=journals&amp;utm_content=101560960&amp;fc=None&amp;ff=20250318181017&amp;v=2.18.0.post9+e462414<description> Liver diseases, including viral hepatitis, alcoholic liver disease (ALD), metabol